  "provider_reasoning_summaries": [
    "Let me analyze the reaction to identify the roles of reagents, solvent, and catalyst.\n\nThe reaction SMILES is:\nC=CC(OC(=O)OC)c1ccccc1.CC#N.O=C(c1ccccc1)N(O)c1ccccc1.[Pd].c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1.c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1.c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1.c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1>>O=C(c1ccccc1)N(OC/C=C/c1ccccc1)c1ccccc1\n\nLet me identify each component:\n\n1. **C=CC(OC(=O)OC)c1ccccc1** - This is cinnamyl methyl carbonate (allylic carbonate with phenyl group). This is an allylic substrate that provides the allyl group.\n\n2. **CC#N** - Acetonitrile (MeCN) - This is a solvent.\n\n3. **O=C(c1ccccc1)N(O)c1ccccc1** - This is benzoyl phenyl hydroxylamine (N-hydroxy-N-phenylbenzamide). This is the nucleophile that attacks the allyl group.\n\n4. **[Pd]** - Palladium - This is the catalyst (metal catalyst for Tsuji-Trost reaction).\n\n5. **c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1** (x4) - This is triphenylphosphine (PPh3) - This is a ligand for the palladium catalyst.\n\nThe product is: O=C(c1ccccc1)N(OC/C=C/c1ccccc1)c1ccccc1 - This is the N-allylated product where the hydroxylamine has been allylated.\n\nThis is a **Tsuji-Trost allylation** reaction:\n- The allylic carbonate undergoes palladium-catalyzed allylic substitution\n- The hydroxylamine acts as the nucleophile\n- Pd(0) with PPh3 ligands is the catalytic system\n- Acetonitrile is the solvent\n\nSo the roles are:\n- **Reagent (substrate)**: C=CC(OC(=O)OC)c1ccccc1 (cinnamyl methyl carbonate - allylic electrophile)\n- **Reagent (nucleophile)**: O=C(c1ccccc1)N(O)c1ccccc1 (N-hydroxy-N-phenylbenzamide - nucleophile)\n- **Solvent**: CC#N (acetonitrile)\n- **Catalyst**: [Pd] (palladium)\n- **Ligand**: c1ccc(P(c2ccccc2)c2ccccc2)cc1 (triphenylphosphine, PPh3)\n\nLet me format this as a condition_role_mapping."
